title: Woman may have been blown into path of road sweeper by Storm Doris
text:
High winds may have been the cause of the accident Credit: Swindon Advertiser/Dave Cox A young woman has died after an accident in Swindon. She may have been blown into path of a road sweeper by high winds.
The 32-year-old was pronounced dead at the scene after the collision. It happened shortly before 4.30pm on Thursday next to the Kingsdown pub.
Police believe she may have been on her way to collect her child. Her next of kin have been informed. An officer said it looked like a tragic accident.
Witnesses have been Quote: d as saying she was blown into path of the vehicle by the storm.
Officers are still investigating.
Last updated Fri 24 Feb 2017
